            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Wallace had received a copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10085.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from A. R. Wallace, 21 July 1875</ref> and n. 1).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref>, pp. 361–3. <hi rend="italic">Utricularia</hi>: baldderwort. <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi>: sundew.</note>
